The paper deals with connections between data structures and cryptography, specifically in the context of the 3SUM problem and preprocessing attacks. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from computational complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), and computational geometry (cs.CG) to derive its results, so these categories are also possible.
